  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nCurrently, we gossip validate local (from the beacon HTTP API) `SignedBlsToExecutionChange` messages before adding them to the op pool. This means we ignore pre-Capella messages. I think the UX would be improved if you could submit locally at any point before the capella fork. It sounds like this is what Prysm intends to implement. ",
